# UI Design System Guide

## Design Principles

### 1. Visual Hierarchy
- Use size, weight, and color to establish importance
- Primary actions should be most prominent
- Group related elements together
- Use whitespace to separate sections

### 2. Consistency
- Maintain consistent spacing (use 4px/8px grid)
- Use a limited color palette (3-5 primary colors)
- Standardize component sizes and behaviors
- Apply typography rules uniformly

### 3. Accessibility
- Minimum contrast ratio of 4.5:1 for text
- Touch targets at least 44x44px
- Provide keyboard navigation
- Include alt text for images
- Support screen readers with ARIA labels

